<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-18T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="285" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/200: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Carter</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-18T16:00:00-05:00">January 18, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. Your 6, January 14, 5 p.m. Johnson will be accompanied by a competent
                            secretary. They sail from Rotterdam February 21. He will keep Embassy at
                            London informed of his movements while in Europe.</p>
                        <p>Wharton is instructed to consult with Johnson at most convenient point in
                            Europe while en route. His travel expenses authorized subject to travel
                            regulations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>